l median 0.06) and network activity ceased\",\n      \"evidence\": \"CPU usage: normal_median=0.06, fault_median=0.0, change_ratio=2.0; Network packets dropped to 0\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"adservice-0\",\n      \"reason\": \"pod_memory_working_set_bytes dropped to 0.0 (from normal median 6030.55) and pod_cpu_usage ceased\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Memory usage: normal_median=6030.55, fault_median=0.0, change_ratio=2.0; CPU usage dropped to 0\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Key Findings:\n\n**Critical Observation**: Multiple pods experienced a complete shutdown during the fault window (07:03:09 to 07:03:10 UTC). The pattern shows:\n- **CPU usage dropped to 0.0** across multiple pods\n- **Network activity ceased** (transmit/receive packets dropped to 0)\n- **Memory usage dropped to 0.0** for some pods\n\nThis suggests a **system-wide service interruption** rather than a single component failure. The affected pods include frontend services (`frontend-0`, `frontend-2`), critical backend services (`productcatalogservice-2`), and advertising services (`adservice-0`).\n\nThe extremely short duration (1 second) and widespread nature of the outage indicate this was likely a **brief system-level event** affecting multiple pods simultaneously, possibly related to infrastructure or orchestration issues rather than application-level problems."}
